[{"id":"/sicp/3.1.1","tag":"TITLE","body":"3.1.1  \n    Local State Variables"},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p1","child":[{"body":"\n    To illustrate what we mean by having a computational object with\n    \n    time-varying state, let us model the situation of withdrawing money\n    from a\n    \n    bank account.  We will do this using a\n    procedure","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":", which takes as argument an\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"amount"},{"body":" to be withdrawn.\n    If there is enough money in the account to accommodate the withdrawal,\n    then ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" should return the balance\n    remaining after the withdrawal.  Otherwise,\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" should return the message\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"EM","child":[{"body":"Insufficient funds.","tag":"#text"}]},{"body":" For example, if we begin with $100\n    in the account, we should obtain the following sequence of responses\n    using\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":":\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":1,"eval":true,"prependLength":9,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6AjCgUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xACMBDAG0uIGMzkAGZgSgxwJLMwHdCAFwAW2AE6U+ISgFsA9gFdigjiDWZC+EJgB8AXgo06jafKUq0aq5nK4A5iW0BnXIICEh2g14BaT8bJZRWU2VStw8KovRjCrACIIYicFfCJ6QlxlEHwlbCc40M4BEXFJEAAmAFY2IA","body":"(withdraw 25) ","output":"75"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":2,"eval":true,"prependLength":11,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6AjCgUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xACMBDAG0uIGMzkAGZgSgxwJLMwHdCAFwAW2AE6U+ISgFsA9gFdigjiDWZC+EJgB8AXgo06jafKUq0aq5nK4A5iW0BnXIICEh2g14BaT8bJZRWU2VStw8KovRjCrACIIYicFfCJ6QlxlEHwlbCc40M4BEXFJEAAmAFYOLGLRCSkqtiA","body":"(withdraw 25) ","output":"50"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":3,"eval":true,"prependLength":13,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6AjCgUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xACMBDAG0uIGMzkAGZgSgxwJLMwHdCAFwAW2AE6U+ISgFsA9gFdigjiDWZC+EJgB8AXgo06jafKUq0aq5nK4A5iW0BnXIICEh2g14BaT8bJZRWU2VStw8KovRjCrACIIYicFfCJ6QlxlEHwlbCc40M4BEXFJEAAmAFYOLGLRCSkqmv4herKANnYgA","body":"(withdraw 60) ","output":"\"Insufficient funds\""},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":4,"eval":true,"prependLength":15,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6AjCgUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xACMBDAG0uIGMzkAGZgSgxwJLMwHdCAFwAW2AE6U+ISgFsA9gFdigjiDWZC+EJgB8AXgo06jafKUq0aq5nK4A5iW0BnXIICEh2g14BaT8bJZRWU2VStw8KovRjCrACIIYicFfCJ6QlxlEHwlbCc40M4BEXFJEAAmAFYOLGLRCSkqmv4herKANnYi1tKpZGqgA","body":"(withdraw 15) ","output":"35"},{"body":"\n    Observe that the expression\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"(withdraw 25)"},{"body":",\n    evaluated twice, yields different values.  This is a new kind of\n    behavior for a\n    procedure.\n    Until now, all our\n    procedures\n    could be viewed as specifications for computing mathematical functions.\n    A call to a\n    procedure\n    computed the value of the function applied to the given arguments,\n    and two calls to the same\n    procedure\n    with the same arguments always produced the same\n    result.","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"FOOTNOTE_REF","id":"#footnote-link-1","body":"1","href":"/sicp/3.1.1#footnote-1"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p2","child":[{"body":"\n        To implement ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":", we can use a\n\tvariable ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" to indicate the balance of\n\tmoney in the account and define ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":"\n\tas a\n        procedure\n        that accesses ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":".\n      \n    The ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":"procedure\n    checks to see if ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" is at least as large\n    as the requested ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"amount"},{"body":".  If so,\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" decrements\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" by ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"amount"},{"body":"\n    and returns the new value of ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":". Otherwise,\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" returns the ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"EM","child":[{"body":"Insufficient funds","tag":"#text"}]},{"body":"\n    message. Here are the\n    definitions\n    of ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" and\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":":\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":5,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6AjCgUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xACMBDAG0uIGMzkAGZgSgxwJLMwHdCAFwAW2AE6U+ISgFsA9gFdigjiDWZC+EJgB8AXgo06jafKUq0aq5nK4A5iW0BnXIICEh2g14BaT8bJZRWU2VStw8KovRjCrACIIYicFfCJ6QlxlEHwlbCc40M4BEXFJEAAmAFY2IA","body":"(define balance 100)\n\n(define (withdraw amount)\n   (if (>= balance amount)\n     (begin (set! balance (- balance amount))\n            balance)\n     \"Insufficient funds\")) "},{"body":"\n    Decrementing ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" is accomplished by the \n    expression","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":6,"eval":false,"body":"(set! balance (- balance amount))"},{"body":"\n        This uses the ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"set!"},{"body":" special form, whose\n\tsyntax is\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":true,"eval":false,"body":"\n(set! $\\langle \\textit{name} \\rangle$ $\\langle \\textit{new-value}\\rangle$)\n\t  "},{"body":"\n    Here\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"body":"$\\langle \\textit{name} \\rangle$","tag":"LATEX"},{"body":"\n\tis a symbol \n      \n    and\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"body":"$\\langle \\textit{new-value} \\rangle$","tag":"LATEX"},{"body":"\n    is any expression.  \n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"Set!"},{"body":" \n    changes\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"body":"$\\langle \\textit{name} \\rangle$","tag":"LATEX"},{"body":"\n    so that its value is the\n    result obtained by evaluating\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"body":"$\\langle \\textit{new-value}\\rangle$","tag":"LATEX"},{"body":".\n      \n    In the case at hand, we are changing ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" so\n    that its new value will be the result of subtracting\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"amount"},{"body":" from the previous value of\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":".","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"FOOTNOTE_REF","id":"#footnote-link-2","body":"2","href":"/sicp/3.1.1#footnote-2"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p3","child":[{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"Withdraw"},{"body":" also uses the\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"begin"},{"body":" \n\tspecial form to cause two expressions to be evaluated in the case where\n\tthe ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"if"},{"body":" test is true: first decrementing \n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" and then returning the value of \n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":". In general, evaluating the\n\texpression\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":7,"eval":false,"body":"(begin $\\textit{exp}_{1}$ $\\textit{exp}_{2}$ $\\ldots$ $\\textit{exp}_{k}$)"},{"body":"\n\tcauses the expressions ","tag":"#text"},{"body":"$\\textit{exp}_{1}$","tag":"LATEX"},{"body":"\n\tthrough ","tag":"#text"},{"body":"$\\textit{exp}_{k}$","tag":"LATEX"},{"body":" to be evaluated in\n\tsequence and the value of the final expression\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"body":"$\\textit{exp}_{k}$","tag":"LATEX"},{"body":" to be returned as the\n\tvalue of the entire ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"begin"},{"body":"\n\tform.","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"FOOTNOTE_REF","id":"#footnote-link-3","body":"3","href":"/sicp/3.1.1#footnote-3"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p4","child":[{"body":"\n    Although ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" works as desired, the\n    variable ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" presents a problem.  As\n    specified above, ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" is a name defined\n    in the\n    global environment and is freely accessible to be examined or\n      modified by any\n      procedure.\n      It would be much better if we could somehow make\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" internal to\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":", so that\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" would be the only\n      procedure\n      that could access ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" directly and\n      any other\n      procedure\n      could access ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" only indirectly\n      (through calls to ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":").  This would\n      more accurately model the notion that\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" is a local state variable used by\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" to keep track of the state of the\n      account.\n  ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p5","child":[{"body":"\n    We can make ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" internal to\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" by rewriting the definition as\n    follows:\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":8,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6AjCgUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xFIHcBaCwgFwAtsAnAQwrRBEwBtc7umAEaserYgGMyyAAwyAlPM5duYgLZDsrbqzUB7AK7E6SlSsyF83AHwBeECLGSyuw8dNnzQ3AHMS3AGd+AEIHUXEpbiowp0jXIxMPT2SuRwjcJM8AIghiAIN8IglCXGMQfCNsAKzFRSA","body":"(define new-withdraw\n  (let ((balance 100))\n    (lambda (amount)\n      (if (>= balance amount)\n        (begin (set! balance (- balance amount))\n               balance)\n        \"Insufficient funds\")))) "},{"body":"\n        What we have done here is use ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"let"},{"body":" to\n\testablish an environment with a local variable\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":", bound to the initial value 100.\n        Within this local environment, we use\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"lambda"},{"body":" to create a procedure that takes\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"amount"},{"body":" as an argument and behaves like our\n        previous ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" procedure.  This\n        procedure—returned as the result of evaluating the\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"let"},{"body":" expression—is\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"new-withdraw"},{"body":",\n        which behaves in precisely the same way as\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" but whose variable\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" is not accessible by any other\n        procedure.","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"FOOTNOTE_REF","id":"#footnote-link-4","body":"4","href":"/sicp/3.1.1#footnote-4"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p6","child":[{"body":"\n    Combining \n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"set!"},{"body":" \n        with local variables \n      \n    is the general programming\n    technique we will use for constructing computational objects with\n    local state.  Unfortunately, using this technique raises a serious\n    problem: When we first introduced\n    procedures,\n    we also introduced the substitution model of evaluation\n    (section ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"1.1.5","href":"/sicp/1.1.5"},{"body":") to provide an\n    interpretation of what\n    procedure\n    application means.  We said that applying a\n    procedure\n    should be interpreted as evaluating the\n    body of the procedure\n    with the\n    formal\n    parameters replaced by their values.\n    \n    The trouble is that,\n    as soon as we introduce assignment into our language, substitution is no\n    longer an adequate model of\n    procedure\n    application.  (We will see why this is so in\n    section ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"3.1.3","href":"/sicp/3.1.3"},{"body":".)  As a consequence, we\n    technically have at this point no way to understand why the\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"new-withdraw"},{"body":"procedure\n    behaves as claimed above.  In order to really understand a\n    procedure\n    such as\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"new-withdraw"},{"body":",\n    we will need to develop a new model of\n    procedure\n    application.  In section ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"3.2","href":"/sicp/3.2"},{"body":" we will\n    introduce such a model, together with an explanation of \n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"set!"},{"body":" and local variables.\n    First, however, we examine some variations on the theme established by\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"new-withdraw"},{"body":".","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p7","child":[{"body":"\n    The following\n    \n\tprocedure, ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"make-withdraw"},{"body":",\n      \n    creates \"","tag":"#text"},{"body":"withdrawal processors.","tag":"#text"},{"body":"\"\n    The formal parameter\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" in\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"make-withdraw"},{"body":"\n    specifies the initial amount of money in the\n    account.","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"FOOTNOTE_REF","id":"#footnote-link-5","body":"5","href":"/sicp/3.1.1#footnote-5"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":9,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6AjCgUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xEwFsBDAa1wFoB3QgFwAtsAnKxkAIyoAbKsQDGuAJRoQMzMIp9sVclQoB7AK7EWUmXvKF85AHwBefkJHiQqzdt379mPrgDmJcgGdcLAIQXhMTJMegCrMlstHQdHWL0BQPEY2IAiCGJPDXwiUUJcbRB8LWxPFIlyjBwCEjIAdWRyajomVg5uXmQABk6KqqJSEFqAJkbaBmZ2Lh4QLp6JIA","body":"(define (make-withdraw balance)\n   (lambda (amount)\n      (if (>= balance amount)\n         (begin (set! balance (- balance amount))\n                balance)\n         \"Insufficient funds\"))) "},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"Make-withdraw"},{"body":"\n    can be used as follows to create two objects ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"W1"},{"body":"\n    and ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"W2"},{"body":":\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":10,"eval":true,"prependLength":8,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6AjCgUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xEwFsBDAa1wFoB3QgFwAtsAnKxkAIyoAbKsQDGuAJRoQMzMIp9sVclQoB7AK7EWUmXvKF85AHwBefkJHiQqzdt379mPrgDmJcgGdcLAIQXhMTJMegCrMlstHQdHWL0BQPEY2IAiCGJPDXwiUUJcbRB8LWxPFIlyjBwCEjIAdWRyajomVg5uXmQABk6KqqJSEFqAJkbaBmZ2Lh4QLp6JIA","body":"(define W1 (make-withdraw 100))\n(define W2 (make-withdraw 100)) "},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":11,"eval":true,"prependLength":11,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6AjCgUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xEwFsBDAa1wFoB3QgFwAtsAnKxkAIyoAbKsQDGuAJRoQMzMIp9sVclQoB7AK7EWUmXvKF85AHwBefkJHiQqzdt379mPrgDmJcgGdcLAIQXhMTJMegCrMlstHQdHWL0BQPEY2IAiCGJPDXwiUUJcbRB8LWxPFIlyjBwCEjIAdWRyajomVg5uXmQABk6KqqJSEFqAJkbaBmZ2Lh4QLp6pLHqQAFYeoA","body":"(W1 50) ","output":"50"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":12,"eval":true,"prependLength":13,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6AjCgUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xEwFsBDAa1wFoB3QgFwAtsAnKxkAIyoAbKsQDGuAJRoQMzMIp9sVclQoB7AK7EWUmXvKF85AHwBefkJHiQqzdt379mPrgDmJcgGdcLAIQXhMTJMegCrMlstHQdHWL0BQPEY2IAiCGJPDXwiUUJcbRB8LWxPFIlyjBwCEjIAdWRyajomVg5uXmQABk6KqqJSEFqAJkbaBmZ2Lh4QLp6pLHqQAFYeyuGQAHYeoA","body":"(W2 70) ","output":"30"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":13,"eval":true,"prependLength":15,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6AjCgUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xEwFsBDAa1wFoB3QgFwAtsAnKxkAIyoAbKsQDGuAJRoQMzMIp9sVclQoB7AK7EWUmXvKF85AHwBefkJHiQqzdt379mPrgDmJcgGdcLAIQXhMTJMegCrMlstHQdHWL0BQPEY2IAiCGJPDXwiUUJcbRB8LWxPFIlyjBwCEjIAdWRyajomVg5uXmQABk6KqqJSEFqAJkbaBmZ2Lh4QLp6pLHqQAFYeyuGQAHZVhZGAFh6gA","body":"(W2 40) ","output":"\"Insufficient funds\""},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":14,"eval":true,"prependLength":17,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6AjCgUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xEwFsBDAa1wFoB3QgFwAtsAnKxkAIyoAbKsQDGuAJRoQMzMIp9sVclQoB7AK7EWUmXvKF85AHwBefkJHiQqzdt379mPrgDmJcgGdcLAIQXhMTJMegCrMlstHQdHWL0BQPEY2IAiCGJPDXwiUUJcbRB8LWxPFIlyjBwCEjIAdWRyajomVg5uXmQABk6KqqJSEFqAJkbaBmZ2Lh4QLp6pLHqQAFYeyuGQAHZVhZGAFm3MRf2JIA","body":"(W1 40) ","output":"10"},{"body":"\n    Observe that ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"W1"},{"body":" and \n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"W2"},{"body":" are completely independent objects, each\n    with its own local state variable ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":".\n    Withdrawals from one do not affect the other.\n  ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p8","child":[{"body":"\n    We can also create objects that handle\n    \n    deposits as well as\n    withdrawals, and thus we can represent simple bank accounts.  Here is\n    a\n    procedure\n    that returns a \"","tag":"#text"},{"body":"bank-account object","tag":"#text"},{"body":"\" with a specified initial\n    balance:\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":15,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6AjCgUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xEwFsBDAa1wFoqBjJgewFdiAXEAIyoA2VYk1wBKNCCk4CJMpgDuhLgAtsAJyoKQVCh24SpR8oXzkAfAF4+g4aJ17OXQ8eOZeuAOYlyAZ1xcAIQ2QiLy9CF2ZLr6zi6uCUb8oaLxiVIARBDEvuz4REyEuNwg+JzYvhli8TJEpOR4AA6svsoOsWnS-kGRYeQA1L32MU7Vkq7JUTV4dfLYhL6NVFxMKiAUneRsxNjkmLgAjgD86yAA5EqqGlpiIJdqmgqbCZj7x6dnTS3Kt1+tzuN0tJcAJ-ORcOp1Kx1CAMgBVYg0YisBTEEDqQ7sXC+HgRCIAWQAggBpACi9EJUCgAHk4QA5AAqGUBQMSG2q8Xmi2WqwkWBmch0LHI1DojBYsRAyAADNKxq9mExzvdrk8QABWOVAA","body":"(define (make-account balance)\n   (define (withdraw amount)\n      (if (>= balance amount)\n         (begin (set! balance (- balance amount))\n                balance)\n            \"Insufficient funds\"))\n   (define (deposit amount)\n      (set! balance (+ balance amount))\n      balance)\n   (define (dispatch m)\n      (cond ((eq? m 'withdraw) withdraw)\n            ((eq? m 'deposit) deposit)\n            (else (error \"Unknown request - - MAKE-ACCOUNT\"\n                   m))))\n   dispatch) "},{"body":"\n    Each call to ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"make_account"},{"body":" sets up an\n    environment with a local state variable ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":".\n    Within this environment, ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"make_account"},{"body":" defines\n    procedures","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"deposit"},{"body":" and\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"withdraw"},{"body":" that access\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"balance"},{"body":" and an additional\n    procedure","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"dispatch"},{"body":"\n    that takes a \"","tag":"#text"},{"body":"message","tag":"#text"},{"body":"\" as input and returns one of the two local\n    procedures.\n    The ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"dispatch"},{"body":"procedure\n    itself is returned as the value that represents the bank-account object.\n    This is precisely the \n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"EM","child":[{"body":"message-passing","tag":"#text"}]},{"body":" style of programming that we saw in\n    section ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"2.4.3","href":"/sicp/2.4.3"},{"body":", although here we are using\n    it in conjunction with the ability to modify local variables.\n  ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p9","child":[{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"Make-account"},{"body":"\n    can be used as follows:\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":16,"eval":true,"prependLength":17,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6AjCgUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xEwFsBDAa1wFoqBjJgewFdiAXEAIyoA2VYk1wBKNCCk4CJMpgDuhLgAtsAJyoKQVCh24SpR8oXzkAfAF4+g4aJ17OXQ8eOZeuAOYlyAZ1xcAIQ2QiLy9CF2ZLr6zi6uCUb8oaLxiVIARBDEvuz4REyEuNwg+JzYvhli8TJEpOR4AA6svsoOsWnS-kGRYeQA1L32MU7Vkq7JUTV4dfLYhL6NVFxMKiAUneRsxNjkmLgAjgD86yAA5EqqGlpiIJdqmgqbCZj7x6dnTS3Kt1+tzuN0tJcAJ-ORcOp1Kx1CAMgBVYg0YisBTEEDqQ7sXC+HgRCIAWQAggBpACi9EJUCgAHk4QA5AAqGUBQMSG2q8Xmi2WqwkWBmch0LHI1DojBYsRAyAADNLqkA","body":"(define acc (make-account 100)) "},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":17,"eval":true,"prependLength":19,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6AjCgUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xEwFsBDAa1wFoqBjJgewFdiAXEAIyoA2VYk1wBKNCCk4CJMpgDuhLgAtsAJyoKQVCh24SpR8oXzkAfAF4+g4aJ17OXQ8eOZeuAOYlyAZ1xcAIQ2QiLy9CF2ZLr6zi6uCUb8oaLxiVIARBDEvuz4REyEuNwg+JzYvhli8TJEpOR4AA6svsoOsWnS-kGRYeQA1L32MU7Vkq7JUTV4dfLYhL6NVFxMKiAUneRsxNjkmLgAjgD86yAA5EqqGlpiIJdqmgqbCZj7x6dnTS3Kt1+tzuN0tJcAJ-ORcOp1Kx1CAMgBVYg0YisBTEEDqQ7sXC+HgRCIAWQAggBpACi9EJUCgAHk4QA5AAqGUBQMSG2q8Xmi2WqwkWBmch0LHI1DojBYsRAyAADNKxlhMMwmOd7tcniAAKxyoA","body":"((acc 'withdraw) 50) ","output":"50"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":18,"eval":true,"prependLength":21,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6AjCgUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xEwFsBDAa1wFoqBjJgewFdiAXEAIyoA2VYk1wBKNCCk4CJMpgDuhLgAtsAJyoKQVCh24SpR8oXzkAfAF4+g4aJ17OXQ8eOZeuAOYlyAZ1xcAIQ2QiLy9CF2ZLr6zi6uCUb8oaLxiVIARBDEvuz4REyEuNwg+JzYvhli8TJEpOR4AA6svsoOsWnS-kGRYeQA1L32MU7Vkq7JUTV4dfLYhL6NVFxMKiAUneRsxNjkmLgAjgD86yAA5EqqGlpiIJdqmgqbCZj7x6dnTS3Kt1+tzuN0tJcAJ-ORcOp1Kx1CAMgBVYg0YisBTEEDqQ7sXC+HgRCIAWQAggBpACi9EJUCgAHk4QA5AAqGUBQMSG2q8Xmi2WqwkWBmch0LHI1DojBYsRAyAADN